{
  "stem": "6130.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I went 40 times in one night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And I was scared stiff, because many times I couldn't hold it to the latrines.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I just had to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And if they would have seen me, they would say, you know, Jewish dirt, or whatever they called us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH]-- we were always called [NON-ENGLISH], which means men.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Then, while I was there, I was also called a horse, because I and a very nice woman, who wasn't even Jewish-- her husband was Jewish, and he got there.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She got there, because she didn't want to be separated from her husband.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She wasn't Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were the horses.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had to pull a wagon up to a place where they had a warehouse and pull back the wagon with bags of sauerkraut, and potatoes, and salt, and what have you-- terrible heavy and hard.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we pulled it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Even pulling the wagon up on-- going up on a mountain was heavy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Coming down it was-- coming down, if we-- should be easier.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But it was terrible heavy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And that damn soldier [LAUGHS] who was guarding us with a gun, every once in a while made us stop-- which was wonderful-- and went to the barrel-- it was a barrel of sauerkraut-- and took out a big handful one or twice, and looks at us.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He says, this is really good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "This is very healthy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But he never-- [LAUGHS] he never gave us anything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "He gave-- he told us how good it was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Anyhow, once on the way back, we caught a soldier, a Canadian who was parachuting-- obviously-- and he was hiding.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I noticed him-- looking-- good-looking.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "He are a redhead guy.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
